<HEAD>Explosion Rips Through Factory On Vesuvius Slope; Two Killed.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ERCOLANO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion that ripped through a
fireworks factory on the side of the Vesuvius volcano killed two
people, wounded three and produced panic in nearby towns, police
said.
   <DATE>Monday</DATE>'s explosion was heard up to a half-mile away and the
inhabitants of nearby hamlets thought the volcano was erupting,
authorities said. Several firetrucks and a helicopter arrived from
nearby <LOCATION>Naples</LOCATION> and doused the flames.
   Police said they did not know the cause of the blast.
   The victims were workers at the factory, which produced
skyrockets.
   Vesuvius last erupted in <DATE>1944</DATE>.
</TEXT>
